      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THAILESS (3) has been a long time since a win and deserves to break through. Placed 6/8 at the trip and 2/2 here. Rates highly and gets chance. SILVER CLIFF (2) didn't make an impact at her last run before going for a spell on August 16, finishing ninth and beaten 4.5 lengths over 1400m at Caulfield. Rates highly this far easier grade and should take some beating. SARDONIAN (4) drifted back and never threatened when sixth last start over 1325m at Geelong. Big chance to find winning form on home track. BALLYNACALLY (1) is a promising type who scored at her only run last prep 12 weeks ago over 1000m at Terang. Sharpened up by a recent trial placing. Yet to run a bad race and does go well fresh. Can play a role in the finish. TRIOMPHE (5) is going well. In a suitable race and is a definite top three chance.",
